2011 Libyan civil war: Rebel forces in Libya retake the town of Ajdabiya from troops loyal to Muammar Gaddafi, and later recapture Brega. (BBC) (Al Jazeera)10 people are reported shot dead around the Israel-Lebanon border (near Maroun al-Ras in Lebanon), as a crowd try to enter Israel through a border fence. Protesters also pelt Lebanese security forces and Israeli soldiers with stones. Over a hundred enter the Israeli-controlled Golan Heights, with 4 shot dead, after Palestinians and Syrians crossed the de facto Israel-Syria border. Over 45 are injured in total.(Christian Science Monitor) (Voice of America) (The Jerusalem Post) (Nowlebanon) (Haaretz)Nigerian soldiers raid suspected militant camps in the Niger Delta in a new offensive. (Reuters)